app

Class Opus

  • java.lang.Object
    • app.Opus
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Opus
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Represents the text taken from a Source in a formatted manner. An Opus contains a title, author, ordinal number, documents (paragraphs), words, raw text, a file name, and file pointer.
    Author:
    David Wickizer
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
